snippet.textDisplay:
What none army's/fans see in them: talented, funny, supportive, understandable, the kind of friends we'll never get, humble & others.
Aside from all those wanna know why the are the biggest boyband in the world?
Their bond with the fans are really strong too. Bts builded up their own platforms from the beginning without a big company helping them. Their compony which is named bighit entertainment isn't one of the big companies but their artis worked hard and achieve something so meaningful like this. I'm not saying that the big company's artists are not talented and humble or something. No, infact I also stan alot of the groups from the company. What im pointing out here is that bts which is before used to have a small amount of fans, who used to share one small apartment, who used to worked day and night to reach their dreams. Bts worked hard for this and boom haters be like 'nah if we wanna hate let us do it' . Well, fine then like bts said themselves 'haters gonna hate players gonna play, live a life man' - Namjoon, mic drop, 2017. Thank you

snippet.textDisplay: I was always curious about this group, as their fans are so vocal about them on social media. I never wanted to know more, however, bcs I was afraid I might end up freefalling into the fandom. However, I couldn't stop myself from watching this since carpool karaoke is one of my fav segments. This is fun to watch! I decided to look for more about them, and I stumbled upon Run! BTS... they're much much sillier and funnier there, it's crazy I know their names now hahah.. see this is what I was afraid of, it's starting to come true. Fyi, kpop is never my cup of tea, but it's so easy to fall for BTS (once you throw away prejudices, of course)!
